        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2020-05-27 20:20:35.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI don't think this works. If lp in lnet_handle_find_routed_path() is the final destination, then you don't want to iterate through its peer nets. It would make sense to use the remote net in the final destination NIDs. Otherwise you might run into a situation where you select a remote net that goes over a router which doesn't have a connection to the final destination NID.\n\nIn that function, it then makes more sense to lookup the remote net of the final destination NID if you know you're routing a message and then jump right to the point where you call lnet_find_route_locked()",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
